\description{
Aliasing probe for the debug-only \verb{&mut [T]} guard (#1104).

Takes two mutable integer slices and increments each. When the caller binds the \emph{same} R vector to both parameters (\code{alias_probe(x, x)}), the macro-generated wrapper emits a \verb{debug_assert!} that panics \emph{before} conversion, because the two \verb{&mut [i32]} slices would alias one buffer (undefined behavior). The assert is compiled out in release builds, so use \code{debug_assertions_enabled} to decide whether to expect the error.

